    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-07T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-07T06:00:00-05:00" n="253"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111Y2/2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJE1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-07T11:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 8, 5 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>399. Department’s 290, February 24 [<hi rend="italic">27</hi>], 3 p.m.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d253fn1">Not printed.</note> and 292 [<hi rend="italic">291</hi>],
                    February 27, 4 p.m. Spanish Ambassador Berlin reports that Spanish Embassy
                    doctor visited <hi rend="italic">Yarrowdale</hi> prisoners at Brandenburg on 1st
                    instant and stated that conditions were as reported by German authorities and
                    approved of the quarantine. The case of typhus occurred on February 20 and
                    quarantine will end March 7 unless new cases occur. The doctor said men
                    complained of diet and were glad to hear of approaching release and had no other
                    complaint. Of the 57 Americans only 5 were in the hospital suffering from <pb
                        facs="0385" n="213" xml:id="pg_213"/> slight colds and 5 men of different
                    nationality are under medical observation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
